{
  "stem": "2067.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It's about a place 15 to 20 miles southeast of Amsterdam where Max knew a gentile-- very nice gentile family-- who had said to him once if there is any danger, you can come to my house at any time.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We had the choice either to pedal along the river Amstel-- the river of Amsterdam-- or to cross a bridge, which was the shorter way.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "For some unknown reason, which I cannot explain, we decided to-- to bicycle along the river Amstel only to hear later on that on both sides of the bridge SS men were standing and arresting any young guy who looked Jewish.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We made it to that place, and stayed there for a week, until we heard that everything had quieted down.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We were still in those days under the totally wrong impression that all the anti-Jewish measures of the Nazis were meant against young men-- young Jewish men-- whom they may consider as soldiers, let's say-- enemy soldiers; and that women and children and the elderly would be allowed to live peacefully.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "I must admit I lived in a dream world still.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I imagined things.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "I should have known better.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But when a couple of months after that round-up, the parents-- parents of our friends, most of friends were caught in those days at that time.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "They all were going to play tennis.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And on the way to the tennis courts in those streets they were all caught. 90% of them were caught.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Two months later, postcards arrived to the parents that their son had died of pneumonia, of typhoid fever, of any kind of imaginary illness, and that they should send 30 marks for the ashes.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "That opened my eyes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Said they are-- they are out to murder us.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
